server = PJFServer(configuration=PJFConfiguration(Namespace(ports={
    'servers': {'HTTP_PORT': 8080, 'HTTPS_PORT': 8443}}, html=False, level=
    6, command=['radamsa'], stdin=True, json={'a': 'test'}, indent=True,
    strong_fuzz=False, url_encode=False, parameters=[], notify=False, debug
    =False, content_type='text/plain', utf8=False, nologo=True)))
server.run()
time.sleep(2)
json_http = urllib2.urlopen('http://127.0.0.1:8080').read()
try:
    import requests
    requests.packages.urllib3.disable_warnings()
    json_https = requests.get('https://127.0.0.1:8443', verify=False).content
    self.assertTrue(json_https)
except ImportError:
    pass
self.assertTrue(json_http)
server.stop()
